00:20:48.740 --> 00:20:51.980
We use sharp cuts on
surfaces like the buttons

00:20:51.980 --> 00:20:55.460
and on larger
sheets of material.

00:20:55.460 --> 00:20:59.210
And those are all tied back to
that diamond logo, the product

00:20:59.210 --> 00:21:02.810
logo of Shrine itself.

00:21:02.810 --> 00:21:05.750
Those aren't just
aesthetic choices.

00:21:05.750 --> 00:21:08.450
When we do those surface
cuts on the corner,

00:21:08.450 --> 00:21:11.960
we're also communicating how the
different material surfaces are

00:21:11.960 --> 00:21:15.050
arranged in the space
and how the user might

00:21:15.050 --> 00:21:18.010
be able to interact with
them in different ways.

00:21:18.010 --> 00:21:22.090
So from front to back, you
have the backdrop back layer,

00:21:22.090 --> 00:21:26.080
which is where we have a custom
navigation menu for Shrine.

00:21:26.080 --> 00:21:28.982
In the middle, we have
the backdrop front layer,

00:21:28.982 --> 00:21:31.440
which is where the bulk of the
content the user is actually

00:21:31.440 --> 00:21:33.910
going to engage with
is going to reside.

00:21:33.910 --> 00:21:35.530
And then the
shopping cart sheet,

00:21:35.530 --> 00:21:38.830
which is actually tucked
almost entirely off screen,

00:21:38.830 --> 00:21:39.970
is foremost.

00:21:39.970 --> 00:21:44.080
And it just gets out of the
view when it's not needed.

00:21:44.080 --> 00:21:47.800
On tablet and desktop,
Shrine's primary navigation

00:21:47.800 --> 00:21:49.090
is through tabs.

00:21:49.090 --> 00:21:53.580
And in keeping with the emphasis
on storytelling through shape,

00:21:53.580 --> 00:21:55.630
we're using a
highlight indicator

00:21:55.630 --> 00:21:57.730
